  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of rust-bindgen</title>

    <para>
      Install <application>rust-bindgen</application> by running the following
      commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>cargo build --release</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      To test the results, issue: <command>cargo test --release</command>. Four
      tests, <filename>header_issue_544_stylo_creduce_2_hpp</filename>,
      <filename>header_constified_enum_module_overflow_hpp</filename>,
      <filename>header_typedef_pointer_overlap_h</filename>, and
      <filename>header_nsbasehashtable_hpp</filename>, are known to fail.
      <!-- https://github.com/rust-lang/rust-bindgen/issues/3318 was reported
      by a user, but there is a commit that fixes it:
      https://github.com/rust-lang/rust-bindgen/commit/9366e0af8da529c958b4cd4fcbe492d951c86f5c
      Given that we're only experiencing problems during the tests though,
      let's just document it for now. -->
    </para>

    <para>
      Now, as the &root; user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>install -v -m755 target/release/bindgen /usr/bin</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Still as the &root; user, install the Bash and Zsh completion
      support files:
    </para>

<screen role='root'><userinput>bindgen --generate-shell-completions bash \
    &gt; /usr/share/bash-completion/completions/bindgen
bindgen --generate-shell-completions zsh  \
    &gt; /usr/share/zsh/site-functions/_bindgen</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

